    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.70-71_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">70</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Elementary <hi rend="caps">ENGLISH
                        <lb/>
                    300 GREGORY HALL : URBANA, ILLINOIS
                        <lb/>
                    
                    ORGAN OF THE
                        <lb/>
                    NATIONAL COUNCIL OF TEACHERS OF ENGLISH
                        <lb/>
                    
                    JOHN J. DEBOER
                        <lb/>
                    EDITOR</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 18, 1959</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route #7 "Skyrim"</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Under separate cover we are sending you a copy of the February issue of <hi rend="underline">Elementary English</hi>, which contains an article by Mrs. Louise <hi rend="caps">H.</hi> Mortensen entitled, "Neihardt's <hi rend="caps">Red Cloud</hi> as Choral Reading."</p>
                
                <p>Mrs. Mortensen assured me that she had cleared with you before publishing this article and quoting from your poem.</p>
                
                <p>In behalf of the National Council of Teachers of English and of this magazine, I wish to extend sincere thanks to you for permitting us to use these quotations from your great poem. We are very proud indeed that we were able to feature this discussion of <hi rend="underline">Red Cloud</hi> and to make this work available to teachers for instructional purposes. I know that both the teachers and the children will derive much inspiration and pleasure from the experience.</p>
                
                <p>With every good wish.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>J. J. DeBoer</signed>
                    <signed>J. J. DeBoer
                    Editor</signed>
                
                    <note>JJDB:e</note>
                </closer>
                
                    <note>cc: Mrs. Mortensen</note>
                    
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.70-71_0002"/>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    Elementary <hi rend="caps">ENGLISH
                        <lb/>
                    300 GREGORY HALL
                        <lb/>
                    URBANA, ILLINOIS</hi>
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    URBANA, ILL.
                    MAR 18
                    330 PM
                    1959
                    
                    PRAY
                    FOR
                    PEACE
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>U.S. POSTAGE 3¢
                    IN GOD WE TRUST
                    LIBERTY</p>
                </figure>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>1 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>WASHINGTON
                    1¢
                    U.S. POSTAGE</p>
                </figure>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">71</fw>
                
                <note type="recipient">ansd</note>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route #7 "Skyrim"</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
            </div1>
